                                         TEHRAN - A powerful quake of magnitude 6.3 struck southeastern Iran near the city of Kerman on Friday, the US Geological Survey said. The quake, which was relatively shallow, was centred 50 km northeast of Kerman, which has a population of more than 821,000. A magnitude 6.3 quake is considered strong and is capable of causing sever damage.